commit.message:
Deprecate and ignore the --backlog option

When I ported socket-burst-dampener to go and rust, I found that there
was no adjustable backlog setting for socket listeners exposed. I've
taken this as an indication that the option is not really needed,
since the value of the net.core.somaxconn sysctl or socket.SOMAXCONN
is likely to suffice.

Signed-off-by: Zac Medico <zmedico@gmail.com>

Suppress ResourceWarning: subprocess 1234 is still running
README.md: add note about tcp_max_syn_backlog sysctl for Linux

Replace epoll loop with asyncio + SIGCHLD handling

This fixes an issue with the epoll loop consuming 100% cpu
due to endless EPOLLHUP events triggered when the subprocess
closes stderr early (observed with rsync).

Explicitly unregister proc.stderr file descriptor (cosmetic)

According the the epoll(7) man page, closed file descriptors are
automatically removed from all epoll sets.
